# Derived. Everything here is reproducible from the sources next to it.
#
# build/ is 573 MB: the headless engine, the pak128 testbed, the game roots and
# every .pak we have ever compiled. It also used to be the only place the test
# scenarios existed, so `rm -rf build` deleted the tests. They live in
# tests/scenarios/ now and are copied in.
build/

# dist/ is written by tools/build_standalone_linter.py and tools/make_figures.py.
# Ignored deliberately, not by accident: a published artefact that CAN be
# committed is a published artefact that can go stale without anyone noticing.
# This one already did - the shipped linter was hours older than its own source.
# Build it at release time, from a known commit.
dist/

# Written by assets/*/blender/build.py. The sprite sheets are the important
# entry here: Blender's metadata stamp wrote the author's absolute path into
# every one of them. Keeping them out of the history means that cannot be
# committed even once.
assets/*/renders/
assets/*/sprites/
assets/*/dat/
assets/*/pak/
assets/*/reports/

# Reference photographs of real vehicles. Not ignored because they are derived -
# ignored because we do not own them. This repository is meant to carry a licence,
# and a licence that covered these would be a false statement about somebody
# else's photographs.
assets/refs/
assets/*/references/

__pycache__/
*.pyc
*.pak
*.zip

# Blender writes a .blend1 backup beside every save. Noise.
*.blend1
